<paragraph id="193A36E4FFB9046EECF9FC8EFD5F8B3F" blockId="32.[151,1436,152,1144]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis id="2BF1EAF6FFB9046EECF9FC8EFE908CD7" bold="true" box="[198,364,886,912]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Observations</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName id="DE854D67FFB9046EEDADFC8FFD2B8CD7" authorityName="Leme &amp; L. Kollmann" authorityYear="2011" box="[402,727,887,912]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Vriesea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="santaleopoldinensis">
<emphasis id="2BF1EAF6FFB9046EEDADFC8FFD2B8CD7" box="[402,727,887,912]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">Vriesea santaleopoldinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="DE854D67FFB9046EEFF6FC8FFAE48CD7" authority="Leme (1999: 163)" authorityName="Leme" authorityPageNumber="163" authorityYear="1999" box="[969,1304,886,912]" class="Liliopsida" family="Bromeliaceae" genus="Vriesea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rafaelii">
<emphasis id="2BF1EAF6FFB9046EEFF6FC8FFBC78CD7" box="[969,1083,887,912]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="33">V.rafaelii</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="7D144B15FFB9046EE87CFC8EFAE48CD7" author="Leme, E. M. C." box="[1091,1304,886,912]" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" pagination="135 - 168" refId="ref22365" refString="Leme, E. M. C. (1999) New Species of Brazilian Bromeliaceae: A Tribute to Lyman B. Smith. Harvard Papers Botany 4 (1): 135 - 168." type="journal article" year="1999">Leme (1999: 163)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished by the leaf blades that bear dense and minute wine spots near the base (vs. green with darker green longitudinal lines and not spotted), by peduncle bracts densely wine spotted (vs. without spots), floral bracts reaching 1/3 of sepal length (vs. reaching 1/2 of sepal length) and densely white spotted (vs. without spots). The flowers are more numerous (ca. 27 vs. ca. 
<quantity id="DE7D9B01FFB9046EEF24FBE9FCAA8B6C" box="[795,854,1041,1067]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.556" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" unit="in" value="14.0">14 in</quantity>
number) with longer pedicels (ca. 
<quantity id="DE7D9B01FFB9046EE8CAFBE9FAB58B6C" box="[1269,1353,1041,1067]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" unit="mm" value="15.0">15 mm</quantity>
vs. ca. 
<quantity id="DE7D9B01FFB9046EECA8FBC0FF158B15" box="[151,233,1080,1106]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 mm</quantity>
long), wine spotted sepals (vs. without spots) and by the petals with a narrowed apex and longer basal appendages (ca. 
<quantity id="DE7D9B01FFB9046EED66FBA6FE578B3F" box="[345,427,1118,1144]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" unit="mm" value="17.0">17 mm</quantity>
vs. ca. 
<quantity id="DE7D9B01FFB9046EEE3BFBA6FDAA8B3F" box="[516,598,1118,1144]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="32" pageNumber="33" unit="mm" value="14.0">14 mm</quantity>
long).
</paragraph>
